{
  "texts": [
    "A way to model this uncertainty is to assume that a future pair object-label is a random variable (X, Y) taking values in X × Y.",
    "Let P denote the probability distribution foot_0 of (X, Y).",
    "The expected prediction mistake is thus E (X,Y)∼P [ℓ(f (X), Y)].",
    "This is usually refered to as the (generalization) risk of f.",
    "As it is a very important notion in machine learning, we introduce the notation"
  ]
}